 * RangeFreqQuery obj = new RangeFreqQuery(arr);
 * int param_1 = obj.query(left,right,value);
 */

Understanding the LogicTo visualize why this works, consider the array 
[12, 33, 4, 33, 22]. The index list for value 33 would be [1, 3]. 
If the query is left=0, right=2, value=33:upperBound(indices, 2) looks
 for the first index strictly greater than 2, which is index 3. 
 This is at position 1 in the list.lowerBound(indices, 0) looks for the first 
 index greater than or equal to 0, which is index 1. This is at position 0 in the 
 list.Result: $1 - 0 = 1$. (Only one occurrence of 33 exists between index 0 and 2).